# LAMMPS Tutorial manifest file. This file determines what is downloaded when.
# comments start with a # as the first character.
# comments and empty lines are ignored
##############################################################################
# Tutorial 1: Crystalline metals and the EAM potential
#
# 1) input file templates
# the first file will be automatically loaded
initial.lmp
minimize.lmp
shifted.lmp

# 2) support files
Al_zhou.eam.alloy

# 3) solution files
# only downloaded on request
# (solution/Al_zhou.eam.alloy is a symlink to ../Al_zhou.eam.alloy so the
#  potential is not duplicated; LAMMPS-GUI resolves the redirect on download)
solution/Al_zhou.eam.alloy
solution/initial.log
solution/minimize.log
solution/shifted.log
solution/render.lmp
# units/potential-conversion demonstration: same single-point energy as
# initial.lmp but in real units (auto-converted via the UNITS: tag)
solution/initial-real.lmp
solution/initial-real.log
# potential-comparison variants (solution only): different potentials,
# same fcc Al calculation, reported in the text as a "proof with numbers"
solution/minimize-Al_mm.lmp
solution/minimize-Al_mm.log
solution/Al_mm.eam.fs
solution/minimize-AlSiMgCuFe.lmp
solution/minimize-AlSiMgCuFe.log
solution/AlSiMgCuFe.meam
solution/library.meam
